Class Period

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dukascopy.api.Period
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Period>

    public final class Period
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Period>, java.io.Serializable
    Represents periods of bars. This class is used as enum in java 1.5 and later, but defined as class to allow creation of custom period.

      • createCustomPeriod

        public static Period createCustomPeriod(Unit unit,
                        int unitsCount,
                        JFTimeZone jFTimeZone)
        This method returns custom period with given JFTimeZone. If jFTimezone is null, then default is used (JFTimeZone.UTC).
        For units smaller than Unit.Day JFTimeZone can have time offsets no other than 0 (JFTimeZone.UTC). If desired period is equal to one of the basic periods, the the appropriate basic period will be returned.

        For the JFTimeZone impact on data loading, please see JFTimeZone javadocs.

        Parameters:
        unit -
        unitsCount -
        jFTimeZone -
        Returns:
        Period - a desired period.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if jFTimeZone has offset from UTC time other than 0 and the given unit is smaller than Unit.Day, or if the desired period is not compliant.

      • createCustomPeriod

        public static Period createCustomPeriod(Unit unit,
                        int unitsCount)
        Method creates custom Period. Note, that the desired period has to be compliant to Period.getCompliancyPeriod() period. If desired period is not compliant, then IllegalArgumentException will be thrown. If desired period is equal to one of the basic periods, the the appropriate basic period will be returned. Returned period's shift will be 0.
        Parameters:
        unit -
        unitsCount -
        Returns:
        Period
